history.content:
"If I take 70, I want to take 61B and 170."

Taking 61B and 170 concurrently sounds like trouble. The start of 170 assumes you understand 61B. It's certainly doable -- I know people who've done it -- but I haven't met anyone who recommended it.

On the other hand taking 70 and 61C sounds okay. If you're set on one of those two paths exactly, I'd recommend taking 61BL. This also keeps you on the well-trodden path of 61A then 61B.

children.subject: I recommend taking CS70 and CS61C. I'm doing that right now and it's been good. CS170 relies a lot on 61B knowledge whereas CS70 and CS61C have no overlap at all.

history.content: I'm having trouble deciding between which one to take. Which one would be easier over summer? I'm taking 61A right now and if I take 61BL I would take 61C and 70 next fall. If I take 70, I want to take 61B and 170.
history.subject: 61BL vs 70 over summer?
